ata-title=&quot;Low bandwidth VP9 (180P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;VP9 180P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;180p.vp9.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;240&quot; data-height=&quot;180&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;175240&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/3/34/Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv/Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv.240p.vp9.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp9, opus&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small VP9 (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;VP9 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.vp9.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;320&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;249728&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/3/34/Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv/Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv.240p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small WebM (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;320&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;256664&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\"><img alt=\"File:Annabelle Serpentine.ogv\" style=\"width:220px;height:165px\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv/220px--Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv.jpg\" /><a href=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/34/Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv\" title=\"Play media\" target=\"new\"><span class=\"play-btn-large\"><span class=\"mw-tmh-playtext\">Play media</span></span></a></div>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Annabelle_Serpentine.ogv\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A segment from Annabelle Butterfly &amp; Serpentine Dances</div></div></div>\n<p>The Serpentine Dance was a frequent subject of early <a href=\"/wiki/Motion_pictures\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Motion pictures\">motion pictures</a>, as it highlighted the new medium's ability to portray movement and light.  Two particularly well-known versions were <i><a href=\"/wiki/Annabelle_Serpentine_Dance\" title=\"Annabelle Serpentine Dance\">Annabelle Serpentine Dance</a></i> (1894), a performance by Broadway dancer <a href=\"/wiki/Annabelle_Whitford\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Annabelle Whitford\">Annabelle Whitford</a> from <a href=\"/wiki/Edison_Studios\" title=\"Edison Studios\">Edison Studios</a>, and a <a href=\"/wiki/Lumi%C3%A8re_brothers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lumi\u00e8re brothers\">Lumi\u00e8re brothers</a> film made in 1896.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Many other filmmakers produced their own versions, distributing prints that had been <a href=\"/wiki/Film_tinting\" title=\"Film tinting\">hand-tinted</a> to evoke (though not quite reproduce) the appearance of colored light projection.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Serpentine_dance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Serpentinen_Tanz\" title=\"Serpentinen Tanz\">Serpentinen Tanz</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Serpentine_dance&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-light-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-light_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-light_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></su